+# Quickstart: Native Parity Surface and Conformance
+
+This guide covers testing the new endpoints and the conformance suite introduced in Phase 7.
+
+## Endpoints
+
+### 1. Safe Domain Endpoints
+```bash
+# Check margin for an order
+curl -X GET "http://localhost:8001/margin-check?symbol=EURUSD&action=0&volume=0.1&price=1.1000" -H "Authorization: Bearer test"
+
+# Calculate profit
+curl -X GET "http://localhost:8001/profit-calc?symbol=EURUSD&action=0&volume=0.1&price_open=1.1000&price_close=1.1050" -H "Authorization: Bearer test"
+```
+
+### 2. Expert Namespace Endpoints
+```bash
+# Raw margin check
+curl -X GET "http://localhost:8001/mt5/raw/margin-check?symbol=EURUSD&action=0&volume=0.1&price=1.1000" -H "Authorization: Bearer test"
+
+# Raw profit calculation
+curl -X GET "http://localhost:8001/mt5/raw/profit-calc?symbol=EURUSD&action=0&volume=0.1&price_open=1.1000&price_close=1.1050" -H "Authorization: Bearer test"
+
+# Market book
+curl -X GET "http://localhost:8001/mt5/raw/market-book?symbol=EURUSD" -H "Authorization: Bearer test"
+
+# Terminal info
+curl -X GET "http://localhost:8001/mt5/raw/terminal-info" -H "Authorization: Bearer test"
+
+# Account info
+curl -X GET "http://localhost:8001/mt5/raw/account-info" -H "Authorization: Bearer test"
+
+# Last error
+curl -X GET "http://localhost:8001/mt5/raw/last-error" -H "Authorization: Bearer test"
+```
+
+## Conformance Harness
+
+Run the conformance suite against a running bridge instance:
+
+```bash
+python -m app.conformance --base-url http://localhost:8001 --api-key test --output-json /tmp/conformance.json
+```
+
+Include write tests (creates and cancels test orders):
+
+```bash
+python -m app.conformance --base-url http://localhost:8001 --api-key test --output-json /tmp/conformance.json --include-write-tests
+```
